############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
In the expression [`\frac{6x^{3}}{2x^{7}}\text{,}`] the coefficients reduce using the properties of fractions. One way to simplify the variable powers is:

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
\frac{6x^{3}}{2x^{7}} \amp= \frac{6}{2} \cdot \frac{x^{3}}{x^{7}}\\
\amp= 3 \cdot x^{3-7}\\
\amp= 3 \cdot x^{-4}\\
\amp= 3 \cdot \frac{1}{x^4}\\
\amp= \frac{3}{x^4}
\end{aligned}
```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

