############################################################
# Solution
############################################################

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
In the expression [`4\left(\frac{1}{5}tv^{-4}\right)^{2}\text{,}`] the exponent [`2`] applies to each factor inside the parentheses.

[```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
\begin{aligned}
4\left(\frac{1}{5}tv^{-4}\right)^{2} \amp= 4\left(\frac{1}{5}\right)^{2}\left(t\right)^2\left(v^{-4}\right)^2\\
\amp= 4\left(\frac{1}{25}\right)\left(t^2\right)\left(v^{-4\cdot 2}\right)\\
\amp= 4\left(\frac{1}{25}\right)\left(t^2\right)\left(v^{-8}\right)\\
\amp= 4\left(\frac{1}{25}\right)\left(t^2\right)\left(\frac{1}{v^{8}}\right)\\
\amp= \frac{4t^2}{25v^{8}}
\end{aligned}
```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

